Micro Focus: Results
MITRE Engenuity does not assign scores, rankings, or ratings. The evaluation results are available to the public, so other organizations may provide their own analysis and interpretation - these are not endorsed or validated by MITRE.
 

Previous Next
Previous Next

Alerting Strategy

Events that match analytic logic for malicious behaviors are assigned appropriate severity values (Very Low, Low, Medium, High, Very High). These alerted events are also enriched with contextual information, such as a title related to the adversary behavior and mappings to related ATT&CK Tactics and Techniques. Indicators potentially associated with compromise are aggregated and highlighted (color coding).

Correlation Strategy

The Event Inspector view captures system events and data, these events can contain contextual information such as process lineage or interactions between processes and files. Events are aggregated to give a wider perspective, while search queries can be used to refine results. Dashboard views exist that summarize events on a per host and/or username basis.
